Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve the @corn on the cob{1} by running a #knife{} firmly around the middle then snapping with your hands. Put the @honey{15%ml} in a #mixing bowl{} with the @shawarma spice mix{1/2%tsp} and a drizzle of @oil{}. Stir together, then add the @British chicken thighs{4}. Mix with your hands so each drumstick gets a good coating. Set aside.

> TIP: If you're not keen on spice, use slightly less shawarma.

> TIP: Be sure to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1/2}(peeled and chopped into roughly 1cm pieces). Halve then remove the core from the @bell pepper{1/2}(halved, cored and chopped into 1cm pieces) and chop into 1cm pieces. Chop the @medium tomato{1}(chopped into roughly 2cm chunks). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @black beans{1/2%400g can} in a #colander{}.

Put the drumsticks on a #baking tray{} along with the corn on the cob. Drizzle some @oil{} over the corn and season everything with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{pinch}. Pop on the top shelf of your oven. Roast for ~{30-35%minutes}.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat and add the onion. Cook until softened, ~{5%minutes}. Add the pepper, a good pinch of salt and a grind of black pepper. Cook for another ~{5%minutes}. Add the tomato and garlic and stir together. Cook for ~{1%minute} longer. Then add the black beans, @basmati rice{150%g}, @light coconut milk{100%ml}, @chicken stock powder{1/2%tsp} and @water{200%ml}.

Bring your mixture to the boil (making sure the stock powder has dissolved), then reduce the heat to a simmer and pop the #lid{} on (or cover with some #foil{}). Cook for ~{10%minutes}. Then remove from the heat and set aside to rest for ~{10%minutes} more. The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). When everything is cooked, remove the chicken and corn from your oven. Stir the parsley through the rice and serve with the chicken and corn on top. Enjoy!